SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 985
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to recognize and honor Erwin Utilities Authority,
the Tennessee Center for Performance
Excellence's 2025 Excellence Award recipient.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should recognize
those businesses that have a long-standing commitment to providing exceptional service to their
customers; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary entity is Erwin Utilities Authority of Unicoi County,
which recently received the 2025 Tennessee Center for Performance Excellence (TNCPE)
Level 4 Excellence Award; and
WHEREAS, the TNCPE Excellence Award was created to recognize organizations that
demonstrate superior performance through well-integrated processes, strong leadership, and
sustained results, which is evaluated using the nationally recognized Baldridge Excellence
Framework; and
WHEREAS, this award confirms that Erwin Utilities Authority's mission, vision, and
SERVICE values (Safety, Efficiency, Reliability, Vision, Integrity, Collaboration, and Excellence)
are embedded in their daily work, operations, and community service; and
WHEREAS, the employees of Erwin Utilities Authority show up every day focused on
their customers' needs and the community; the Excellence Award affirms that the work they do
represents the best in Tennessee and their commitment to continuous improvement and
responsible service; and
WHEREAS, Erwin Utilities Authority has worked tirelessly to improve the lives of citizens
in the community, and it is most fitting that the business be honored on this special occasion;
now, therefore,
SJR0985
016346
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we recognize and honor Erwin Utilities Authority, the
Tennessee Center for Performance Excellence's 2025 Excellence Award recipient, extending
our best wishes for continued success in all further endeavors to compassionately and
devotedly serve others.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
